majesty /ˈmædʒɪstɪ/

(majesties) 

1. N-VOC/PRON You use majesty in expressions such as Your Majesty or Her Majesty when you are addressing or referring to a king or queen. 陛下 [poss PRON] [礼貌] 

例： His Majesty requests your presence in the royal chambers. 国王陛下要求你在皇室受召见。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Majesty is the quality of being beautiful, dignified, and impressive. 壮丽; 雄伟 

例： ...the majesty of the mainland mountains. …大陆山岳的壮美。

